,Recommended,465360,23253332,"Posted: 28 May, 2016",all,☣ Broken Ninja ☠,"This is one of the founding fathers of the FPS/RTS hybrid type games. You play as an advanced Wraith Hover Tank. You have a large arsenal of weapons you can upgrade to as you play through each Planetary & Solar System campaign, you build & defend your bases and call in units whether they be infantry, tanks, aav or bombers on the fly as you conquer through each map. Not bad for a nearly 20 year old game... wait... what? I just realized how old it was... im gettin' old... *facepalm*Bought this to see if it was finally optimized to at least play on Windows 7. While it does, its definitely a dated classic. I own the disc version, but had to make some tweaks with that version to get it to play stable enough where it wouldnt CTD (crash to desktop) every 10 minutes or have random UI glitches just like its sequel Uprising 2 Lead & Destroy had. With this version its the Software mode version, not the 3dfx Glide version with smoother textures. However I do have nGlide installed and even though its running software mode by default it picked up the nGlide wrapper which was cool and possibly gave the steam version a little more stability.As is, this game series was a cult classic, not widely popular except to those who found it. The only con I can truly say I wish couldve been fixed, was the clunk mouse movement for aiming. There has been no way to fix this manually, it feels like im using an old ball mouse and it rollers are all junked up and sticking making it look like my mouse movements are getting stuck every so often.Edit - This Gamer came out of no where and fixed the problem I had for a long time. ""DarkStarSword - Mouse aiming is easy to fix - in the controls menu set the acceleration slider all the way down and the sensitivity slider all the way up."""
